# KSwitch initial admin credentials — TEMPLATE
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# `make seed` (on laptop / on-prem Docker installs) renders this template
# into ./state/initial-admin.txt with mode 600.
#
# The rendered file is THIS exact format. The audit-log subscriber on
# successful first admin login parses it back to confirm the identity
# and then unlinks it (G20).
#
# Cloud / K8s installs do NOT render this template to disk — the same
# JSON payload (password + valid_until) is written to the cloud-native
# secret manager / K8s Secret instead, per §F lifecycle revision.
#
# Variable expansion happens in scripts/seed.sh:
#   {{CUSTOMER_ID}}  → KSWITCH_CUSTOMER_ID env value
#   {{USERNAME}}     → admin@{{CUSTOMER_ID}}
#   {{PASSWORD}}     → openssl rand -base64 24 (32-char URL-safe)
#   {{VALID_UNTIL}}  → ISO-8601 UTC stamp, +24h from generation
#   {{GENERATED_AT}} → ISO-8601 UTC stamp at generation time
#
# After first admin login, this file is auto-deleted. After {{VALID_UNTIL}}
# the password is rejected by the admin login flow regardless of file
# persistence (time-bomb, G20b). Use `make seed-reset
# KSWITCH_CONFIRM_SEED_RESET=yes` to recover (G21a).
KSWITCH_INITIAL_ADMIN_VERSION=1
KSWITCH_INITIAL_ADMIN_USERNAME={{USERNAME}}
KSWITCH_INITIAL_ADMIN_PASSWORD={{PASSWORD}}
KSWITCH_INITIAL_ADMIN_VALID_UNTIL={{VALID_UNTIL}}
KSWITCH_INITIAL_ADMIN_GENERATED_AT={{GENERATED_AT}}
KSWITCH_INITIAL_ADMIN_CUSTOMER_ID={{CUSTOMER_ID}}
